{"body": "> Calling rails use of rake a \"misuse\" has more to do with twitter-imposed terseness than with the actual way I would categorize it. I do think rails' use of rake is suboptimal and has room for improvement, but that's more nuanced than fits in a tweet.\r\n\r\nYes, that's why I wanted to make sure you came here, and why I made sure to copy the tweet and the (mis?) part of it. The `?` says to me that you weren't trying to make a super big statement, just Twitter. Since you are on the rspec team, I figured that your insight here is important, along with @alindeman's.", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/12744643", "created_at": "2013-01-26T23:45:14Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/9080#issuecomment-12744643", "updated_at": "2013-01-26T23:47:18Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 9080, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/steveklabnik", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/233c279c012ebac792aaa805f966cbc7?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F0c22d45f31acf0f4192c8c12b7a55dee.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik/received_events", "gravatar_id": "233c279c012ebac792aaa805f966cbc7", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "steveklabnik", "type": "User", "id": 27786, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "523d5a22bd354364b900607f"}, "id": 12744643, "issue_url"